Female
– Protarsi present (except 

C. bonariensis

). Head bearing massive, posteriorly curved horn like that of male (except 

C. bellicosus

). Pronotum transversely concave; posterior (dorsal) margin of concavity developed as massive, saddle-shaped prominence usually broader than equivalent prominence in male (except 

C. bellicosus

).
